  section.slide#secure-shell
    h2 Secure Shell (SSH)
    blockquote "cryptographic network protocol for secure data communication, remote command-line login, remote command execution, and other secure network services between two networked computers" - <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Secure_Shell">Wikipedia</a>

  section.slide#ssh
    h2 SSH Client
    ul
      li <tt>ssh</tt>
      li Establishes a secure connection with a remote machine
      li Runs a shell session through the connection
      li Can tunnel other traffic too

  section.slide#ssh-basics
    h2 SSH Basics
    textarea.code(name="code", mode="shell", style="display: none;").
      # start a remote shell session
      $ ssh some.machine.com

      # run a remote command
      $ ssh some.machine.com 'cd my_scripts; ./do_stuff.sh'

      # start a remote shell session on a vagrant box
      $ vagrant ssh

      # copy a file from remote to local
      $ scp some.machine.com:my_scripts/do_stuff.sh .

